      "passage_text": "Directions (Q. Nos. 63-67) In each of the questions below, a group of numerals is given followed by four groups of symbol/letter combinations lettered (a), (b), (c) and (d). Numerals are to be coded as per the codes and conditions given below. You have to find out which of the combinations (a), (b), (c) and (d) is correct and indicate your answer accordingly. If none of the combinations represents the correct code, mark (e) as your answer.\n\nNumerals: 3 5 7 4 2 6 8 1 0 9\nLetter/Symbol code: * B E A @ F K % R M\n\nFollowing conditions apply\n(i) if the first digit as well as the last digits is odd, both are to be coded as X.\n(ii) if the first digit as well as the last digit is even, both are to be coded as $.\n(iii) if the last digit is 'zero', it is to be coded as #.",
